of the Issuers counsel and accountants and reasonable fees and disbursements of one counsel representing any selling stockholders, other than any underwriting discounts and commissions, related to any demand or incidental registration; and
 A lock-up agreement entered into by NBV in connection with the Issuers initial public
offering (the Lock-Up Agreement) pursuant to which NBV has agreed, for a period of 180 days after the initial public offering date set forth in the Final Prospectus, not to (i) offer, sell,
